==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Disconnection
<hw>Dis`con*nec"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act of
disconnecting, or state of being disconnected; separation; want of
union.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Nothing was therefore to be left in all the subordinate members
but weakness, <qex>disconnection</qex>, and confusion.</q>
<rj><qau>Burke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Disconsecrate</ent>⟦br⟧
